#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. Life Span "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Sappasutta "
msgstr "6. A Serpent "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn4.6:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn4.6:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.6:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā rattandhakāratimisāyaṃ abbhokāse nisinno hoti, devo ca ekamekaṃ phusāyati. "
msgstr "Now at that time the Buddha was meditating in the open during the dark of night, while a gentle rain drizzled down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.238, sc2
msgctxt "sn4.6:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā bhagavato bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ uppādetukāmo mahantaṃ sapparājavaṇṇaṃ abhinimminitvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked, wanting to make the Buddha feel fear, terror, and goosebumps, manifested in the form of a huge serpent king and approached him. "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma mahatī ekarukkhikā nāvā; "
msgstr "Its body was like a huge canoe carved from a single tree. "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.3"
msgid "evamassa kāyo hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma mahantaṃ soṇḍikākiḷañjaṃ; "
msgstr "Its hood was like a large brewer’s sieve. "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.5"
msgid "evamassa phaṇo hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma mahatī kosalikā kaṃsapāti; "
msgstr "Its eyes were like those big bronze dishes from Kosala. "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.7"
msgid "evamassa akkhīni bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.8"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma deve gaḷagaḷāyante vijjullatā niccharanti; "
msgstr "Its tongue flickered from its mouth like lightning flashes in a thunderstorm. "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.9"
msgid "evamassa mukhato jivhā niccharati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.10"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma kammāragaggariyā dhamamānāya saddo hoti; "
msgstr "The sound of its breathing was like the puffing of a blacksmith’s bellows. "

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.11"
msgid "evamassa assāsapassāsānaṃ saddo hoti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn4.6:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn4.6:4.1"
msgid "“Yo suññagehāni sevati, "
msgstr "“A self-controlled sage frequents "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:4.2"
msgid "Seyyā so muni attasaññato; "
msgstr "empty buildings for lodging. "

# NOTE: A clear case where carati means"live’, not “wander”.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:4.3"
msgid "Vossajja careyya tattha so, "
msgstr "It’s appropriate for such a person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:4.4"
msgid "Patirūpañhi tathāvidhassa taṃ. "
msgstr "to live there after relinquishing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.107, pts2ed1.239, sc5
msgctxt "sn4.6:5.1"
msgid "Carakā bahū bheravā bahū, "
msgstr "Though there are lots of creepy crawlies, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ḍaṃsasarīsapā → ḍaṃsasiriṃsapā (bj, s1-3, km) | ḍaṃsā siriṃsapā (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn4.6:5.2"
msgid "Atho ḍaṃsasarīsapā bahū; "
msgstr "and lots of flies and snakes, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:5.3"
msgid "Lomampi na tattha iñjaye, "
msgstr "they wouldn’t stir a hair "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:5.4"
msgid "Suññāgāragato mahāmuni. "
msgstr "of a great sage in that empty hut. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn4.6:6.1"
msgid "Nabhaṃ phaleyya pathavī caleyya, "
msgstr "Though the sky may split and the earth may quake, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:6.2"
msgid "Sabbepi pāṇā uda santaseyyuṃ; "
msgstr "and all creatures be stricken with fear; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:6.3"
msgid "Sallampi ce urasi pakappayeyyuṃ, "
msgstr "and even if an arrow’s aimed at their breast, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:6.4"
msgid "Upadhīsu tāṇaṃ na karonti buddhā”ti. "
msgstr "the Buddhas take no shelter in attachments.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn4.6:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ bhagavā, jānāti maṃ sugato”ti dukkhī dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!” miserable and sad, vanished right there."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
